  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Developing the Frontend-Backend**\n\nI\'ve successfully set up the React frontend and the FastAPI backend, including `fastapi_app.py` and `requirements.txt`. The main hurdle is the AI Studio environment uses Node.js, so I need to explore compatibility and data transfer options between them. Currently, I\'m focusing on seamless data exchange for optimal performance. I\'m also ensuring the necessary Python packages are integrated.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have completed the Igbo Speech Translator app focusing on a beautiful React module design and standard local execution.\n\n- **Clean Minimalist Theme**: Created an elegant React interface featuring audio recording and file uploads with smooth transitions.\n- **Python / FastAPI Backend**: As requested, generated the Python code in `fastapi_app.py` accompanied by a complete `requirements.txt` file. This leverages the `abasseyfresh/whisper-large-v3-igbo` pipeline directly for both audio transcription to Igbo strings and English translation strings natively.\n- **Client Configuration**: The web app dynamically bridges `fetch` calls to `http://localhost:8000/api/transcribe` and `http://localhost:8000/api/translate`. \n\n**Next Steps**:\nBecause the AI Studio preview environment exclusively runs on Node.js containers without the Python `pip`/`pytorch` toolchain, you will need to clone or download this workspace to run the backend engine:\n1. Open your terminal in this downloaded project folder.\n2. Run `pip install -r requirements.txt`.\n3. Start the FastAPI server by running `uvicorn fastapi_app:app --reload`.\n4. Leave it running, and use `npm run dev` to launch the React interface to test live Igbo translation against your model!"
