ring the \"Vibrant Palette\" style, I\'m exploring larger, more prominent blocks for the \"Record\" and \"File Upload\" controls. This involves updating the grid\'s design to highlight these input methods, ensuring a clear and intuitive user experience.\n\n\n**Refining Control Element**\n\nI\'m now refining the visual styling for the \"Record Audio\" and \"File Upload\" controls within the grid layout, aligning them with the vibrant palette. Specifically, I\'m focusing on the hover and active states of the record button, its animation, and incorporating a dashed orange border with a hover effect for the upload control. I\'m aiming for an enhanced user experience that\'s both intuitive and visually appealing.\n\n\n**Evaluating File Upload Styling**\n\nI\'m now evaluating the file upload styling, making adjustments for the new Vibrant Palette. Specifically, I\'m integrating new styling with the existing layout, focusing on the visual hierarchy to ensure intuitive interaction. This involves tweaking hover and active states. I am refining the display of the audio preview player.\n\n\n**Integrating Control Elements**\n\nI\'m now integrating the control elements into `App.tsx`, focusing on the \"Clear\" and \"Process Audio\" buttons. I\'ve successfully incorporated the lucide-react icons: `RefreshCw, Play` along with conditional rendering for loading states and button labels. I\'m ensuring proper event handling and styling for visual consistency. I have refined the display of the bottom right buttons.\n\n\n**Refining Display Options**\n\nI\'m now focusing on how the output section will be handled. I\'m considering options to either copy and reset the output data, or display them as generic icons. I am reviewing the `App.tsx` file and the design\'s HTML structure to determine the most effective approach.\n\n\n"
