  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Clarifying the Core Question**\n\nI\'m focusing on the user\'s direct question about Node.js, noting they want a simple answer without modifications, unlike their FastAPI request. The user explicitly stated they want me to respond in a normal, chat-like format. The need to answer why Node.js is my only choice is the current key point of this analysis.\n\n\n**Justifying the Technical Constraints**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on a direct answer, emphasizing Google AI Studio\'s Node.js-centric design for its preview environment. The core of this explanation revolves around the sandboxed Cloud Run containers, which prioritize JavaScript/TypeScript execution via Node.js for quick and secure web app deployments. I will also make it very clear that native Python support or large machine learning dependencies aren\'t pre-installed.\n\n\n**Confirming Current Limitations**\n\nI am now emphasizing the limitations of the current preview sandbox. I must reassure the user that their Python code works if run locally. I\'m taking a conversational approach, adhering to my persona as a helpful AI coding assistant, to explain the technical aspects. This requires acknowledging the inherent constraints of the current environment.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "That is a great question! It comes down to how the Google AI Studio live preview environment is engineered. \n\nThe environment you are previewing this app in is a specialized, lightweight sandbox designed for rapid web development. It is fundamentally built around a **Node.js** ecosystem (using tools like Vite, React, and Express). Here is why:\n\n1. **Speed and Standardization**: Node.js allows the platform to instantly bundle, compile, and serve full-stack web applications using a single unified language (JavaScript/TypeScript) for both the frontend and the mock backend.\n2. **Infrastructure Constraints**: Installing Python, PyTorch, audio-processing libraries (like `librosa` or `ffmpeg`), and downloading massive machine learning models (like the Whisper HuggingFace model) requires gigabytes of storage, heavy system-level dependencies, and a completely different runtime engine. The live preview sandboxes are isolated Cloud Run containers that simply aren\'t provisioned for heavy machine learning workloads.\n3. **Security and Sandboxing**: Node.js web servers are highly predictable and easier to securely sandbox and route in a shared cloud environment.\n\nBecause I can only boot up Node.js services in this specific preview window, the Python FastAPI server we wrote conceptually exists in the files but cannot actually *run* here. That is why I designed the app so you can easily export the code to your local machine, where you can spin up the Python backend yourself!"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 4
      nanos: 684712230
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
